        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3402088461" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17578031089228253051">Another tremendous book by Chaim Potok. It is a continuation of the story in <i>The Chosen</i>. It was thought provoking in terms of presenting a number of challenging moral dilemmas, and I was forced to ask myself how I would deal with each scenario as it arose. The writing style is very appealing. The long carnival account in the opening of the book could have easily become boring if written by a less talented writer, but it was written in such a way that I wouldn&apos;t even think of putting the book dow</span>
  <span id="freeText17578031089228253051" style="display:none">Another tremendous book by Chaim Potok. It is a continuation of the story in <i>The Chosen</i>. It was thought provoking in terms of presenting a number of challenging moral dilemmas, and I was forced to ask myself how I would deal with each scenario as it arose. The writing style is very appealing. The long carnival account in the opening of the book could have easily become boring if written by a less talented writer, but it was written in such a way that I wouldn't even think of putting the book down until it was resolved. It dealt fairly with the struggle between religious traditionalism and modernism. <br /><br />I was hoping there might be a third book in this serious, but it appears that is not the case. That saddens me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17578031089228253051" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
