    <a title="Sarah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21619336-sarah"><img alt="Sarah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1407868643p2/21619336.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2705751700?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah" href="/user/show/21619336-sarah">Sarah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2705751700" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7295143284992750294">so, I didnt realize this book was a follow-up to The Chosen. I didnt really enjoy reading it, but I did appreciate it.<br/><br/>this novel brought up some great questions about what parts of tradition we choose to keep, and what we forgo for the sake of modernity, and the uncomfortability of skepticism versus the beauty and comfort of blind faith. certain parts of this book were outdated (psychotherapy procedures, mostly) to the point of distraction. <br/><br/>beautifully written but I kind of couldn&apos;t wait to be d</span>
  <span id="freeText7295143284992750294" style="display:none">so, I didnt realize this book was a follow-up to The Chosen. I didnt really enjoy reading it, but I did appreciate it.<br /><br />this novel brought up some great questions about what parts of tradition we choose to keep, and what we forgo for the sake of modernity, and the uncomfortability of skepticism versus the beauty and comfort of blind faith. certain parts of this book were outdated (psychotherapy procedures, mostly) to the point of distraction. <br /><br />beautifully written but I kind of couldn't wait to be done with it. maybe I should have read The Chosen first?</span>
  <a data-text-id="7295143284992750294" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

