  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/70989037" />
    <a title="Michelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1066546-michelle"><img alt="Michelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1207678483p2/1066546.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/70989037?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle" href="/user/show/1066546-michelle">Michelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1066546-michelle?shelf=novels">novels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer70989037" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11025999811089667968">Another re-read for me. I keep coming back to Potok and learning more each time I do--something that cannot be said for more than a handful of 20th century authors. When Chaim Potok passed away, I remember being heartbroken that there would never be a continuation of the stories of these characters; I had kept hoping against hope. :-) IMO this book is a work of near genius; on the nth read, I still had trouble putting it down. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


