  <span id="freeText17217103500934003705" style="display:none">I am so happy to be in this world with these characters again. This book, like The Chosen, is about fathers and sons and friendship, and it's a remarkable look into a community I don't know much about otherwise. It was so interesting to dive into the tensions between Hasid, Orthodox, and other Jews, and here the influx of refugees after World War II add layers to that tension I would not have expected. The writing is beautiful. There is some experimental psychology that might be triggering for some readers.</span>
