        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128876665-bhavika-solanki?shelf=to-re-read">to-re-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4023968022" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12150531159330771757">(This review is a combined review for &quot;The Chosen&quot; and &quot;The Promise&quot;)<br/><br/>I read &quot;The Chosen&quot; and fell in love with the characters and read &quot;The Promise&quot; shortly after. I haven&apos;t stopped thinking about some of the themes explored in these books; the silence of Reb Saunders, the relationship between Danny and Reuven and their relationships with their fathers, how Michael&apos;s struggles mirror Danny&apos;s pain and Reuven&apos;s frustration, the religious differences and tensions and the passion of learning that bo</span>
  <span id="freeText12150531159330771757" style="display:none">(This review is a combined review for "The Chosen" and "The Promise")<br /><br />I read "The Chosen" and fell in love with the characters and read "The Promise" shortly after. I haven't stopped thinking about some of the themes explored in these books; the silence of Reb Saunders, the relationship between Danny and Reuven and their relationships with their fathers, how Michael's struggles mirror Danny's pain and Reuven's frustration, the religious differences and tensions and the passion of learning that both Danny and Reuven have. Being so invested in the lives of Reuven and Danny, I did not want this series to end! Chaim Potok is a brilliant writer and I will definitely read his other books!</span>
